messages.message:
Configure multi-factor authentication issue...
I was prompted to set up Configure multi-factor authentication. I selected "SMS" but my country code, +44, isn't an option on the list.
This means the country isn’t supported by us. You’ll have to use an Authenticator App
Ah ok, I wonder if a message to the same would be helpful?

I think the selector dropdown UI implies that country codes that are not included aren't a valid option. We also added a tooltip in the previous screen. @hannah thoughts on adding another line in this screen? I like that it is more explicit but it's redundant.
We can, but I think it's redundant. Let's wait for more user feedback accordingly before making another change.
For what it's worth, I didn't clock that tooltip
